defaultValue for MoneydefaultU
defaultnless you understand the true picture of performance, you are denied the opportunity of bei
defaultng able to agree a baseline, 
defaultmake improvements upon it and demonstrate how you are providing greater value for money.
defaultFew would be convinced that recording the crime of theft by pickpocketing as ‘lost property’ would be a sensible approach – nor would recording attempted burglary (where the suspect has attempted to force a window with a crowbar) as ‘Criminal Damage to a dwelling’. Inaccurately recording crimes does not present value for money.
defaultConversely, accurate crime recording allows you to understand the true situation and then put str
defaultategies in place (e.g. PCCs Policing Plan
default) to improve things. If you don’t agree, consider this; Two patients go to see their doctor. One tells him exactly what the symptoms are and gives a full account of how he is affected. The other fails to tell him about some symptoms altogether and only describes other symptoms as less serious than they really are. Which of the two patients stands a better chance of being cured?
