defaultIt is also clear that demographics have a part to play. Areas and populations change and so t
defaultheir demands change too. Is the
default police service responsive to those demands or is there a formula used to decide levels of policing that has not changed for years? Are some officers and police staff horribly overworked, whilst other are comparatively under
default-employed? Do some areas of the
default police service appear to perform well because of their resources – or in spite of them??
defaultDetermining local policing prioritiesdefaultSetting local priorities will be determined by a number of issues – not least of which must be the views of constituents, however, there must also be an understanding of the (accurate) levels of priority crimes and Anti Social Behaviour (ASB). The importance of accurate crime recording is rehearsed above so I shall not repeat it here.
