default7.default              defaultThe British Crime SurveydefaultThe Home Office asserts that the BCS can provide a better reflection of the true level of crime than police statistics since it includes crimes that have not been reported to, or recorded by, the police. The Home Office also claims that it measures crime more accurately than Police statistics since it captures crimes that people may not bother to report because they think the crime was too trivial or the police couldn't do much about it. The BCS also provides a better measure of trends over time since it has adopted a consistent methodology and is unaffected by changes in reporting or recording practices. (Wikipedia)
defaultUntil recently the British Crime Survey and Police Recorded Crime followed roughly the sam
defaulte trajectory, however,
default they
default now 
defaultappear to have parted company.
